WEBVTT

00:42.677 --> 00:43.644
I got your message.

00:43.678 --> 00:45.546
I don't, I don't know
what to think.

00:45.579 --> 00:46.647
I'm on my way.

00:50.484 --> 00:52.086
Please give me a call.

00:52.120 --> 00:54.422
You sounded so upset,
I'm worried.

02:08.763 --> 02:11.065
What's wrong, Nathan?

02:11.099 --> 02:13.701
Something's
happened. Something really bad.

02:29.117 --> 02:31.152
There's
something you should know.

02:31.185 --> 02:33.254
We've never talked about it.

02:33.287 --> 02:36.190
In fact, I never told anyone.

02:36.224 --> 02:39.093
When I was a kid
my parents split up.

02:39.127 --> 02:40.728
I lived with my father.

02:42.396 --> 02:44.565
He and I didn't get along.

02:44.598 --> 02:47.735
It seemed like he never
approved of anything I did.

02:47.768 --> 02:49.838
He had my whole life
mapped out for me.

02:50.972 --> 02:53.607
And he wasn't concerned
about what I wanted.

02:55.243 --> 02:58.746
I met a girl
named Cecilia at Stanford.

02:58.779 --> 03:01.015
I had it really bad for her.

03:01.049 --> 03:02.483
I was gonna marry her.

03:03.584 --> 03:06.187
Until that weekend.

03:06.220 --> 03:08.756
A family friend, Becki
was getting married.

03:08.789 --> 03:11.025
My dad's girlfriend,
Vanessa, was in the wedding,

03:11.059 --> 03:13.694
So Becki had invited them
to stay at her parents' place

03:13.727 --> 03:15.964
On the lake a couple of days
before the ceremony.

03:21.669 --> 03:23.237
My father wasn't social,

03:23.271 --> 03:25.373
So he'd typically start
drinking right away.

03:25.406 --> 03:26.975
Henry.

03:27.008 --> 03:28.609
What?

03:28.642 --> 03:30.778
Make it two, Henry.

03:30.811 --> 03:32.413
- Hey!
- Hey!

03:32.446 --> 03:33.781
No one
really seemed to mind, though.

03:33.814 --> 03:36.250
In fact, people were always
trying to please my father.

03:36.284 --> 03:38.052
Hey, that's a good
single malt I picked up.

03:38.086 --> 03:39.787
Let me know
what you think of that.

03:39.820 --> 03:41.622
I will.

03:41.655 --> 03:43.591
Good thing we got here
before the storm hit.

03:43.624 --> 03:45.826
God, you look good!

03:45.860 --> 03:47.661
Look who's talking.

03:47.695 --> 03:50.464
You cut the hair,
you shaved the goatee.

03:50.498 --> 03:51.732
That's a very sexy look
on you.

03:51.765 --> 03:54.002
- Thank you.
- Hey, easy you two.

03:54.035 --> 03:55.769
Hey, don't worry.

03:55.803 --> 03:57.805
There's only one girl
I'm taking to Fiji.

03:57.838 --> 03:59.007
Oh!

03:59.040 --> 04:00.408
So how about it?
You wanna go to Fiji?

04:00.441 --> 04:02.010
- Hey!
- I'd love it!

04:02.043 --> 04:04.178
Complete asses!

04:04.212 --> 04:05.479
I'm sorry, did I just loose
myself for a minute?

04:05.513 --> 04:06.614
She looks so good.

04:06.647 --> 04:08.149
Okay!

04:08.182 --> 04:09.783
What does every...
What do we need here?

04:09.817 --> 04:11.685
At first, I
wasn't gonna go to the wedding,

04:11.719 --> 04:13.687
But Cecilia
talked me into it.

04:13.721 --> 04:14.822
Look, there's what the law is,

04:14.855 --> 04:16.824
There's what the law
shouldn't be.

04:16.857 --> 04:19.027
You know, I don't understand
why they don't implement

04:19.060 --> 04:21.029
A law that says if you,

04:21.062 --> 04:23.797
Make the loan
you assume the risk,

04:23.831 --> 04:25.699
You manage that risk,

04:25.733 --> 04:27.668
No selling off
to a third party.

04:27.701 --> 04:31.105
You don't understand why they
make the law like that?

04:31.139 --> 04:33.174
No, I don't understand why
they don't make that law,

04:33.207 --> 04:35.609
Why they don't implement
that law.

04:35.643 --> 04:37.711
Well, maybe you should talk
to your congressman.

04:37.745 --> 04:40.781
You know, I mean 'cause
that's how laws get changed.

04:40.814 --> 04:44.718
I'm just ah, working inside
a, you know, a set of rules,

04:44.752 --> 04:47.021
And uh, playing by the rules.

04:47.055 --> 04:48.456
I mean what you're talking
about now

04:48.489 --> 04:51.059
Is changing the rules
in the middle of the game.

04:51.092 --> 04:53.861
And uh, ya know, as long
as the rules are set up

04:53.894 --> 04:55.696
The way they are,
I'm gonna play the best,

04:55.729 --> 04:57.798
You know, I can.
I mean, I mean, you are,

04:57.831 --> 04:59.133
You're in Africa,
you're doing your deal,

04:59.167 --> 05:00.969
But uh, you know,
I got a family and a,

05:01.002 --> 05:02.870
A lot of obligations.

05:02.903 --> 05:05.974
They were always
long-winded political conversations.

05:06.007 --> 05:09.177
They would go on
and on and on.

05:09.210 --> 05:11.112
Nothing ever got solved.

05:12.346 --> 05:16.317
With my father,
it was all about money.

05:16.350 --> 05:18.019
Well, that's my point.
Is that, is that

05:18.052 --> 05:19.687
The situation is able to be
exploited...

05:19.720 --> 05:21.889
It's open!

05:21.922 --> 05:23.691
We'll continue this.

05:23.724 --> 05:24.725
- Hey!
- Oh, wow!

05:24.758 --> 05:28.062
- Ahh, Nathan, you came!
- Oh!

05:28.096 --> 05:30.731
- Hi.
- Hi, Cecilia!

05:30.764 --> 05:32.733
So good to see you.

05:32.766 --> 05:33.567
- Vanessa!
- Hey, how you doing?

05:33.601 --> 05:35.203
Good.

05:35.236 --> 05:38.039
My father didn't
seem very exited to see Cecilia and me.

05:38.072 --> 05:40.541
I wasn't sure you guys were
gonna be able to make it, so,

05:40.574 --> 05:43.244
I kept it a surprise.
Surprise!

05:43.277 --> 05:45.546
This is a surprise.

05:45.579 --> 05:47.948
- Hey!
- Good one, I hope.

05:47.982 --> 05:50.184
Definitely.

05:50.218 --> 05:51.785
- Oh, perfect.
- Hmm-hmm.

05:51.819 --> 05:53.554
No, thank you.

05:53.587 --> 05:55.689
See, that's what
I'm talking about.

05:55.723 --> 05:57.025
It's that simple
"No, thank you"

05:57.058 --> 05:58.459
And look how thin she is.

05:58.492 --> 06:00.761
Wine is low carb.

06:00.794 --> 06:02.930
You really should try some.

06:02.963 --> 06:04.532
Maybe later.

06:04.565 --> 06:08.636
So I'm doing a story on this
group that's building a well

06:08.669 --> 06:12.073
For a village in Zimbabwe.

06:12.106 --> 06:14.075
For 125 dollars,

06:14.108 --> 06:16.644
A whole village
could have clean water.

06:16.677 --> 06:18.646
Wow, that's really cool.

06:18.679 --> 06:21.782
It's true, a woman's
intuition is very perceptive.

06:21.815 --> 06:22.883
Well, I guess mine isn't,

06:22.916 --> 06:24.218
'Cause I didn't have
a fucking clue.

06:24.252 --> 06:25.753
I thought we were driving
to LA

06:25.786 --> 06:27.321
'Cause he was going
to a conference.

06:27.355 --> 06:29.123
We're driving up Highway 1
and, honestly,

06:29.157 --> 06:31.725
I was annoyed because I get
car sick on windy roads.

06:31.759 --> 06:33.161
Oh, my God, tell me about it.

06:33.194 --> 06:35.663
I was sick
the whole way here.

06:35.696 --> 06:38.599
Yeah, and um,

06:38.632 --> 06:41.635
I'm, I'm sitting next
to this old woman,

06:41.669 --> 06:44.004
And her skin is like leather.

06:44.038 --> 06:46.907
It's like she
has so much... depth

06:46.940 --> 06:49.077
And history in her face.

06:49.110 --> 06:51.912
And um, and she's staring
at me.

06:51.945 --> 06:54.815
Now, I'm,
I'm not joking around,

06:54.848 --> 06:57.285
I mean she wasn't being subtle,
she was really staring at me.

06:57.318 --> 07:02.524
And uh, and so I smiled
and it took her a second

07:03.557 --> 07:07.761
And then she smiled back and
her whole being just lit up.

07:09.363 --> 07:11.665
- It was beautiful.
- Wow.

07:11.699 --> 07:12.866
It's sight connection, man,

07:12.900 --> 07:14.835
That's, that's why
I do what I do.

07:14.868 --> 07:16.437
Pulls off by
El Matador beach

07:16.470 --> 07:18.272
And says he wants to look at
the view, so we walk off

07:18.306 --> 07:20.040
To this little side area
and go over this bluff

07:20.074 --> 07:22.710
And overlooking this
incredible ocean view

07:22.743 --> 07:24.945
Is a table
with a white table cloth,

07:24.978 --> 07:27.348
Waiter with a bow tie,
a guy playing a violin...

07:27.381 --> 07:28.982
A violin?

07:29.016 --> 07:31.485
Wow, he went all out.
That's romantic.

07:31.519 --> 07:33.487
And you know the crazy thing
is about this?

07:33.521 --> 07:35.823
Is that I look at him
when I see this

07:35.856 --> 07:37.358
And I'm like...

07:37.391 --> 07:38.859
"Wow, why don't you ever do
anything romantic

07:38.892 --> 07:41.795
Like that for me?"

07:41.829 --> 07:43.131
So he says
"Funny you should ask. "

07:43.164 --> 07:44.965
And he gets down on one knee.

07:44.998 --> 07:46.467
- Pretty amazing.
- Yeah.

07:46.500 --> 07:50.238
Man, um, I wish I could
do something like that.

07:50.271 --> 07:52.806
You should give me a call
when you finish school.

07:52.840 --> 07:55.509
You know, we, um, we're
always looking for interns.

07:55.543 --> 07:57.811
Yeah, I'm, I'm actually done.

07:57.845 --> 08:00.348
I'm not going to grad school.

08:00.381 --> 08:01.349
Oh.

08:01.382 --> 08:02.383
So, what're you gonna do?

08:02.416 --> 08:04.152
I know I don't
want to do that.

08:04.185 --> 08:06.086
Hey, guys, what's shaking?

08:06.120 --> 08:07.721
Well, Nathan
was just telling me how

08:07.755 --> 08:10.524
He's not going
to graduate school.

08:10.558 --> 08:11.559
What?

08:11.592 --> 08:13.927
I hadn't actually
told my father yet.

08:13.961 --> 08:16.230
I've been meaning
to talk to you about that.

08:17.931 --> 08:20.067
Would you excuse us?

08:20.100 --> 08:21.835
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

08:28.742 --> 08:30.378
What the fuck are you
talking about?

08:30.411 --> 08:33.113
You're not going
to grad school?

08:33.147 --> 08:35.783
I thought about it
and I made up my mind.

08:35.816 --> 08:36.917
I... it's not what I wanna do.

08:36.950 --> 08:38.751
You made up your mind?

08:38.785 --> 08:39.919
Yeah.

08:39.953 --> 08:40.953
Do you know how much money

08:40.988 --> 08:43.691
I have invested
in your education?

08:46.227 --> 08:47.761
I mean, it cost me
40,000 dollars

08:47.795 --> 08:49.963
To put you through
first grade.

08:52.132 --> 08:53.801
50,000 dollars
for second grade.

08:53.834 --> 08:56.036
It just went up from there.

08:56.069 --> 08:57.871
It didn't go well.

08:59.940 --> 09:01.575
You're going
to graduate school.

09:01.609 --> 09:03.577
No if, ands, or buts!

09:03.611 --> 09:06.079
That's what I love.

09:06.113 --> 09:07.881
- Hey, I got to run.
- Bye.

09:07.915 --> 09:09.250
So, I'll meet you
at the caterer's later?

09:09.283 --> 09:11.285
Yes, good, yeah.

09:11.319 --> 09:13.387
Becki just told us
about the proposal.

09:13.421 --> 09:15.589
I had no idea you were
such a romantic.

09:15.623 --> 09:17.291
It just took the right girl
to bring it out of me.

09:18.626 --> 09:20.728
Hey, I already said "yes. "

09:20.761 --> 09:22.230
No need to sweet talk me.

09:22.263 --> 09:23.997
Really?
Take it while you can get it.

09:24.031 --> 09:26.066
Yeah, or someone else might.

09:28.035 --> 09:29.737
- What?
- Well...

09:30.838 --> 09:32.072
You better keep
sweet talking.

09:32.105 --> 09:34.975
I guess they've convinced me,
what else you got?

09:35.008 --> 09:36.844
Uh...

09:36.877 --> 09:38.579
I'll think of something
on the drive.

09:38.612 --> 09:39.847
- Okay, it better be good.
- Alright.

09:39.880 --> 09:42.850
- Better be good, love you.
- Love you.

09:42.883 --> 09:45.085
A bachelor's degree doesn't
mean what it used to.

09:45.118 --> 09:46.687
Not in this economy.

09:46.720 --> 09:49.490
I don't understand why
it matters so much.

09:49.523 --> 09:51.124
Because it's your future.

09:51.158 --> 09:52.860
Right, it's my future.

09:52.893 --> 09:55.596
Yeah, and I'm paying
the bills.

09:55.629 --> 09:59.199
You're going to graduate
school, end of story.

09:59.233 --> 10:01.869
Why, so I can end up
like you?

10:01.902 --> 10:03.637
What?

10:03.671 --> 10:05.072
I heard that.

10:09.477 --> 10:11.679
- How are things with you?
- Oh, great.

10:11.712 --> 10:13.314
How are things with you?

10:14.248 --> 10:16.484
Good, good.

10:17.551 --> 10:20.688
So, how are things with
you and Nathan going?

10:21.855 --> 10:23.391
Great, Henry.

10:25.025 --> 10:27.027
You and Vanessa?

10:30.931 --> 10:32.533
Things are pretty good.

10:32.566 --> 10:33.901
Pretty good.

10:34.902 --> 10:36.404
I called you.

10:37.170 --> 10:38.539
I called you back.

10:38.572 --> 10:40.541
Yeah, and I couldn't talk
because I was with Nathan,

10:40.574 --> 10:42.109
So I called you back.

10:43.076 --> 10:45.979
Okay, what do you want?

10:48.916 --> 10:50.818
We need to talk, Henry.

10:52.019 --> 10:53.153
Why?

10:53.186 --> 10:54.588
What's there to talk about?

10:54.622 --> 10:56.089
Because something happened.

10:56.123 --> 10:57.758
It's not something
I can just forget about.

10:57.791 --> 10:59.293
Okay, alright.

11:01.762 --> 11:02.996
Talk, what do you wanna know?

11:03.030 --> 11:04.097
What do you wanna talk about?

11:04.131 --> 11:06.199
- Oh, my God, really?
- What?

11:07.568 --> 11:12.005
- Let's talk about this.
- Okay, alright.

11:14.308 --> 11:16.344
- Okay.
- Okay.

11:16.377 --> 11:17.611
Okay.

11:18.479 --> 11:20.247
What happened...

11:21.715 --> 11:23.150
It was...

11:24.552 --> 11:25.519
It was pretty passionate.

11:25.553 --> 11:28.088
Yeah, yeah.

11:28.121 --> 11:30.057
It was pretty passionate.

11:31.158 --> 11:35.262
So, I was just thinking that...

11:37.965 --> 11:40.067
Maybe you and me would be...

11:41.969 --> 11:45.272
You wanna sh...

11:45.305 --> 11:47.040
You wanna keep it up?

11:49.009 --> 11:50.944
I'm, I'm, I'm down.

11:51.779 --> 11:55.616
- Really?
- Definitely, definitely.

11:55.649 --> 11:58.218
Looking back
on it, I guess there were signs.

11:58.251 --> 12:03.090
Cool, but, you know, we got
to be really careful.

12:03.123 --> 12:04.592
I mean, really careful.

12:04.625 --> 12:06.960
- Yeah, yeah.
- Alright?

12:06.994 --> 12:09.630
I can just tell by the way
his eyes light up

12:09.663 --> 12:12.466
When he looks at her.

12:12.500 --> 12:13.967
He's gonna ask her
to marry him.

12:15.268 --> 12:17.571
- You really think so?
- Mm-hmm.

12:19.507 --> 12:21.675
That's all we
fucking need, man.

12:22.943 --> 12:24.912
And I really think
it's a second chance for you

12:24.945 --> 12:27.180
And Nathan to connect
and bond.

12:27.214 --> 12:29.082
It's about time
for that to happen.

12:30.451 --> 12:32.152
Yeah, maybe you're right.

12:33.554 --> 12:35.589
I know that you didn't wanna
come with me this weekend,

12:35.623 --> 12:38.526
But it means a lot
to me that you came.

12:38.559 --> 12:40.027
Thank you.

12:40.060 --> 12:42.430
No, I'm, I'm glad I came.

12:42.463 --> 12:45.032
This could be a nice time.

12:45.065 --> 12:48.502
You know, we got a little
time before dinner.

12:52.573 --> 12:53.941
You're talking
about five minutes?

12:53.974 --> 12:57.811
I sure am.

12:57.845 --> 13:00.080
I'm good.
I'm down.

13:03.484 --> 13:06.019
Don't you think we should
get back downstairs?

13:06.053 --> 13:08.221
Why?
So I can listen to my dad

13:08.255 --> 13:09.957
Talk to me about
school some more?

13:11.659 --> 13:12.826
He is your dad.

13:12.860 --> 13:13.861
So?

13:13.894 --> 13:15.195
So?

13:15.228 --> 13:18.666
He has the right to be
concerned about your future.

13:18.699 --> 13:20.901
It's not my future
he's concerned about.

13:20.934 --> 13:23.303
It's his status.

13:23.336 --> 13:25.473
He wants what's best
for you, Nathan.

13:25.506 --> 13:27.475
So he says.

13:28.008 --> 13:29.376
Nathan.

13:30.243 --> 13:32.780
Okay, okay.

13:37.217 --> 13:40.220
Hey, do you think uh...

13:40.253 --> 13:42.255
If I go down there
and deal with him,

13:42.289 --> 13:46.159
Maybe I can come back up here
and deal with you a bit?

13:47.628 --> 13:48.896
Maybe.

13:48.929 --> 13:52.466
Maybe as in 80, 90% chance?

13:53.901 --> 13:56.269
We'll see how it goes.

13:56.303 --> 13:58.706
Alright, I have a feeling
it's going to go very well.

14:00.908 --> 14:01.909
Come, come on in.

14:01.942 --> 14:03.410
- Okay, I gotta go, bye.
- Hey.

14:03.443 --> 14:06.747
Hey, so, I'm gonna head out.

14:06.780 --> 14:08.081
- Okay.
- But Evan's gonna stop by.

14:08.115 --> 14:09.282
He wanted to see you
before the wedding.

14:09.316 --> 14:12.553
- Oh, that's great!
- I miss him, how is he?

14:12.586 --> 14:13.687
He's Evan.

14:17.390 --> 14:19.126
He's still trying to figure
out what he's doing

14:19.159 --> 14:20.260
With his life.

14:20.293 --> 14:21.895
I think Evan just needs
to find himself.

14:21.929 --> 14:24.698
Oh, really?
Really?

14:24.732 --> 14:26.133
Why, why do people say that?

14:26.166 --> 14:29.269
- Say what?
- Uh, make excuses for him.

14:29.302 --> 14:31.071
I swear to God,
I love him so much,

14:31.104 --> 14:32.973
But he's never been held
accountable for anything

14:33.006 --> 14:34.207
In is entire life.

14:34.241 --> 14:35.275
What are you talking about?

14:35.308 --> 14:37.144
Well, um, I know you haven't
seen him in a while,

14:37.177 --> 14:38.712
But he's pretty much doing
the same thing

14:38.746 --> 14:41.048
He's always been doing.

14:42.015 --> 14:43.116
Didn't he finish college?

14:43.150 --> 14:46.119
No, it's like,
grow the fuck up already.

14:46.153 --> 14:48.589
You know, I know you
hate it when I compare,

14:48.622 --> 14:50.057
But...

14:50.090 --> 14:51.559
Nathan, who's
ten years younger,

14:51.592 --> 14:53.226
Graduated from Stanford,

14:53.260 --> 14:55.663
Got accepted
to Berkeley Law School...

14:57.330 --> 14:59.733
Nathan's a good kid,
Henry got lucky.

15:01.835 --> 15:03.403
How are you two doing?

15:03.436 --> 15:04.838
We're good.

15:04.872 --> 15:07.775
- Really?
- Yes, we're good.

15:07.808 --> 15:10.443
Look, I know you know about
all the girls...

15:11.478 --> 15:13.146
Yeah, all of 'em.

15:13.180 --> 15:15.749
Yup, the girls,
the drinking, all of it.

15:15.783 --> 15:17.417
But he's a different man now.

15:17.450 --> 15:19.753
We've been together
for two years.

15:19.787 --> 15:21.021
That's true.

15:21.054 --> 15:23.290
And I think, honestly,
I think that was

15:23.323 --> 15:26.627
A turning point for him.
You know, I think solid now.

15:26.660 --> 15:28.629
It's...

15:28.662 --> 15:31.331
Okay, I'm gonna go.

15:31.364 --> 15:32.365
Because the road down
the mountain's

15:32.399 --> 15:34.501
Really rough in the rain.
Yeah.

15:34.534 --> 15:37.771
I'm sorry, I just don't want
to see you get hurt again.

15:37.805 --> 15:39.072
I know.

15:40.407 --> 15:42.275
I love you.

15:43.877 --> 15:47.214
I love you, too.

15:48.248 --> 15:51.018
