in the Great Depression

24:43.583 --> 24:45.318
Or in a panic.

24:47.920 --> 24:49.922
But, wait, if you invested
the money

24:49.956 --> 24:51.191
That your parents
gave you for school,

24:51.224 --> 24:53.726
How did you pay for school?

24:53.760 --> 24:55.728
Oh, I dropped out.

24:55.762 --> 24:58.765
Oh, my gosh!
Were your parents mad?

24:58.798 --> 25:00.333
Well, they didn't know.

25:01.968 --> 25:03.570
I just walked around
in the sweatshirt

25:03.603 --> 25:07.407
And then I talked about
the football team.

25:07.440 --> 25:10.109
My old man never suspected
a thing.

25:10.143 --> 25:12.579
So you lied to them.

25:12.612 --> 25:14.614
Well, that depends
on how you look at it.

25:14.647 --> 25:17.116
I like to think that
I was living my life

25:17.150 --> 25:20.353
The way that I wanted to, so,
in that sense,

25:20.387 --> 25:22.855
I was actually
being more truthful.

25:23.890 --> 25:26.159
Okay.

25:27.827 --> 25:30.963
I'm telling you
all my secrets.

25:30.997 --> 25:32.799
Now it's your turn.
You tell me one.

25:32.832 --> 25:34.133
I don't have any secrets.

25:34.167 --> 25:35.968
Oh, come on,
everyone has secrets.

25:36.002 --> 25:37.370
I don't.

25:37.404 --> 25:39.239
Umm...

25:39.272 --> 25:40.907
Let me guess...

25:43.176 --> 25:44.811
