No!

25:47.079 --> 25:48.315
- Yeah.
- Why would you say that?

25:48.348 --> 25:49.782
I'm, I'm sorry,
I don't want to offend you,

25:49.816 --> 25:52.785
But, it's just something
that, I got the sense that,

25:52.819 --> 25:54.921
You know.

25:54.954 --> 25:56.789
Clearly you think
that you love Nathan,

25:56.823 --> 25:57.990
And I understand that,

25:58.024 --> 26:00.293
But you guys aren't exactly,
you know.

26:01.861 --> 26:02.829
No, I don't know.

26:02.862 --> 26:04.997
You guys aren't exactly
on the same page.

26:05.031 --> 26:06.266
What would make you say that?

26:06.299 --> 26:09.669
- Your body language.
- My body language?

26:09.702 --> 26:11.838
Well, our thoughts, they,

26:11.871 --> 26:14.407
Manifest into the way
that we move, you know,

26:14.441 --> 26:18.645
90 percent of communication
is nonverbal.

26:18.678 --> 26:20.280
I could tell a lot about
people here

26:20.313 --> 26:22.849
Just from what
I saw earlier.

26:22.882 --> 26:24.083
Like what?

26:25.652 --> 26:27.687
Well, like Nathan.

26:28.988 --> 26:31.057
He tries really hard
to be perfect.

26:32.225 --> 26:34.927
And he's an idealist,
but he's conflicted.

26:36.963 --> 26:39.866
Because his heart is telling
him that good guys win,

26:39.899 --> 26:41.934
But his mind has begun
to tell him that guys

26:41.968 --> 26:44.371
Like his father actually win.

26:44.404 --> 26:46.306
Guys like his father.

26:46.339 --> 26:47.674
What do you mean by that?

26:47.707 --> 26:50.710
Guys that take what they want
without apologizing for it.

26:53.880 --> 26:55.548
The things that people tell
you about themselves,

26:55.582 --> 26:59.051
That's really what they want
you to believe, right?

26:59.085 --> 27:01.120
The key is to watch the body,

27:01.153 --> 27:03.723
